1939;;Old Mother Riley, MP;;British;;Oswald Mitchell;;Arthur Lucan, Kitty McShane;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Mother_Riley,_MP;;Concerning Old Mother Riley's fight against her landlord, and as a means of defeating a corrupt politician intent on demolishing her street and the local pub along with it, Mother Riley taking to the soapbox. Local crowds cheer her on, and she finds herself elected to Parliament, and eventually promoted to Cabinet Minister for Strange Affairs.[1][2][3]